oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Camp Linceeda?
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: unknown
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Camp Linceeda?, 1906. Caption: "A Drink Around Camp Linceeda?. Old Cap Maples is seen here second to the left on top row. He had both feet froze off during the war. Here's to our Sweethearts, sisters, and mother. May they all be happy during our absence. Mort." Shows seven men drinking from bottles, near a tent.
